profile_positions.description:
I have been working for the Arnhem Nijmegen City Region since 2008. During the years my work package and experience has grown gradually, alongside with responsibilities. Working in a city region is a challenge: managing the interests of 20 municipalities while keeping regional and national goals on traffic and transport in check. Maintaining good relations with the municipalities is a key factor in regional cooperation.

At the city region I was involved with regional cycling projects, cycling policies and knowledge development on cycling. I am the project manager for the whole program of fast cycling routes in the Arnhem Nijmegen City Region, with currently 6 routes in planning and/or under construction. The program consisted of an investment volume of about € 60mln and 80km of fast cycling routes, (one of) the biggest program in the Netherlands. 
Facilitating cooperation, finding available funding and preparation of political agreements were my main objectives when working on these routes. I've been doing this from the very start of each project, when finances, goals and objectives were still unclear untill the very last phase of the project, where marketing and communication are the main aspects in convincing people to try riding a bike to/from work.
As an experienced project manager I've been a speaker at several (inter)national conferences and meetings, including Velo-city 2013, 2014 and 2015, the Dutch National Cycling Congress and a host for international delegations visiting the Arnhem Nijmegen City Region to learn about our cycling culture, projects and policies.

Other projects I am or have been working on at the Arnhem Nijmegen City Region as a project manager:
- Inland shipping (our region got > € 7mln for inland harbor development from the national government);
- Comprehensive regional and local traffic and transport studies;
- Managing traffic and transport subsidies;
- Developing and implementing a project management system in our ICT system
